						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone in the garden to the east of the village.</hi></p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">A.D. 1780.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1702, Śārvari, Vaiśākha ba. 10</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">May 28, Sunday</hi> (not verifiable), states that <hi rend="bold">Sāhadara Hanumantagauḍa,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">Dēśāyi</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Guttaḷal</hi> bestowed the office of the Accountant <hi rend="italic">(Śānubhōvike)</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Keṁgonḍa</hi> situated in the <hi rend="italic">Mahal</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Kāginele</hi> on a person (not named). A <hi rend="italic">naiar</hi> of 300 <hi rend="italic">varāhas</hi> was taken from him for granting the privilege.</p>						

						</summary>
